Online Education Platform - ER Diagram
&amp; Authentication Design

1. Overview
This document outlines the database Entity-Relationship (ER) design and authentication
system for the online education platform. The system supports three roles: Admin, Teacher,
and Student.

2. Entities and Descriptions
Users
Stores all platform users including admin, teachers, and students.
Teacher Profiles
Contains additional details for teachers such as qualifications, bio, and per-class rate.
Student Profiles
Stores student-specific information.
Courses
Represents courses created by teachers.
Enrollments
Maps students to courses (many-to-many relationship).
Classes
Represents individual sessions/lectures within a course.
Attendance
Tracks student attendance per class.
Earnings
Tracks teacher earnings per completed class.
Assignments
Assignments created by teachers for a course.
Submissions
Student submissions for assignments.

Materials
Notes and learning resources uploaded by teachers.
Reschedules
Handles rescheduling requests for classes.
Calendar Events
Optional table for additional scheduling events.

