4. Authentication System Design
4.1 Authentication Method
JWT (JSON Web Token) based authentication will be used for secure login and session
management.
4.2 Login Flow
1. User submits email and password.
2. Backend verifies credentials.
3. If valid, generate JWT token.
4. Token is returned to client.
5. Client stores token (local storage or cookie).
6. Token is sent with every API request.
4.3 Token Payload
Payload will include:
- user_id
- role (admin/teacher/student)
- email
4.4 Authorization

Role-based access control will be implemented:
- Admin: Full access
- Teacher: Manage courses, classes, assignments
- Student: View courses, attend classes, submit assignments
4.5 Security Measures
- Passwords stored using hashing (bcrypt)
- Token expiration
- HTTPS usage
- Input validation
